{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The structural logic of twenty-eight Buddhas mirrors the astronomical cycle of the lunar mansions. Just as twenty-eight mansions represent a full rotation of the moon, twenty-eight Buddhas represent the full scope of known hagiographic history. While scripture acknowledges that Buddhas are technically infinite across time, the set of twenty-eight serves as the \u8220"complete\u8221" historical lineage preserved by the tradition.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The {\b Atthav\u299 ?sati Paritta} (Protective Chant of Twenty-Eight Buddhas) extends this numerological architecture into liturgical practice, invoking the unique qualities of each Buddha for protection against malevolent forces.\par}
